<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 13 at 8:55PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An area of snow showers will affect southwestern Cuyahoga...
northeastern Medina and northeastern Lorain Counties Until 1030 PM
EST....
At 853 PM EST, radar indicated a snow shower over Avon Lake, or 7
miles northeast of Lorain, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE... Visibility dropping to as low as one quarter of a
mile... Up to 2 inches of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Cleveland, Lorain, Elyria, Parma, Lakewood, Strongsville, Brunswick,
Westlake, North Royalton, North Ridgeville, Avon Lake, North Olmsted,
Garfield Heights, Avon, Parma Heights, Rocky River, Broadview
Heights, Brook Park, Berea and Fairview Park.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
